The development of new THz technologies based on heterostructure architectures and/or nonlinear mechanisms has led to a variety of new insights into underlying current conversion mechanisms, broken symmetries, and fundamental material properties. In heterostructure approaches, laser-driven spin currents are converted into charge currents through so-called inverse processes. Here, interfacial P\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
